aws::graph::propositions: # Hawker 800 Aircraft Accidents
A Hawker 800 operated as ExecuFlight Flight 1526 crashed into an apartment complex in Akron, Ohio on 10 November 2015.
The Hawker 800 crash in Akron occurred shortly before 15:00 Eastern Standard Time.
The Hawker 800 crash in Akron occurred during rainy weather.
The Hawker 800 was on approach to Akron Fulton International Airport when it crashed.
Witnesses reported hearing a loud explosion during the Hawker 800 crash in Akron.
Witnesses reported seeing smoke and flames as the Hawker 800 crash in Akron occurred.
All nine occupants of the Hawker 800 ExecuFlight Flight 1526 were killed in the crash.
Both pilots of the Hawker 800 ExecuFlight Flight 1526 were among those killed in the crash.
The National Transportation Safety Board reported the Akron crash was caused by pilot error.
The National Transportation Safety Board reported the Akron crash was caused by operational issues within the charter company.
The National Transportation Safety Board reported the Akron crash was caused by deficiencies in the Federal Aviation Administration's oversight of the charter operator.
The Federal Aviation Administration's deficiencies specifically involved operations inspections of the charter operator.
A Hawker 800XP crashed near Farmingdale, New York on 20 December 2020.
The Hawker 800XP crash near Farmingdale occurred at 8:35 p.m. Eastern Standard Time.
The Hawker 800XP aircraft faced substantial damage in the Farmingdale crash.
The captain of the Hawker 800XP sustained minor injuries in the Farmingdale crash.
The first officer of the Hawker 800XP was seriously injured in the Farmingdale crash.
The Hawker 800XP was operating as a Part 91 business flight.
The Hawker 800XP was operated by Talon Air, LLC.
The Hawker 800XP flight was operated as a Title 14 Code of Federal Regulations flight.

text:
10 November 2015: A Hawker 800 operating as ExecuFlight Flight 1526 crashed into an apartment complex in Akron, Ohio shortly before 15:00 EST in rainy weather while on approach to Akron Fulton International Airport. Witnesses reported hearing a loud explosion, and seeing smoke/flames as the crash occurred. All nine occupants of the aircraft, including both pilots, were killed. The National Transportation Safety Board reported the crash was caused by pilot error, operational issues within the charter company, and deficiencies in the FAA's oversight (operations inspections) of the charter operator.
20 December 2020: A Hawker 800XP crashed near Farmingdale, New York. At 8:35 p.m. EST the aircraft faced substantial damage; the captain sustained minor injuries, and the first officer was seriously injured. The plane was a Part 91 business flight operated by Talon Air, LLC as a Title 14 CFR.
